election_record.label: New York 1814 State Senate, Western District

overview.note: The Buffalo Gazette (Buffalo, NY) uses the name Bennett Bricknell for Bennet Bicknell, John Pendergast for John J. Prendergast, and Jared Stanford for Jared Sanford.

The Columbian (New York, NY), The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), Otsego Herald (Cooperstown, NY), and The Watch-Tower (Cooperstown, NY) use the name Jared Sandford for Jared Sanford and the middle initial I for John J. Prendergast.
The Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) uses the name J. Townsend for Joshua Forman.
The History of Steuben County uses the name Bennett Becknell for Bennet Bicknell and John J. Pendergast for John J. Prendergast.

Jabez D. Hammond, James Birdsall, Richard Smith, Daniel W. Lewis, Peter B. Porter, Micah Brooks, Oliver Comstock, Enos T. Throop, Seth Phelps, and Emanuel Coryell were candidates for Congress. Robert Monnell, John Guthrie, Thompson Mead, Nathaniel Waldron, Asa Norton, John Fray, Jr., Ethel Bronson, Mark Hopkins, Windsor Comer, David Beecher, Luther Gitteau, Edward S. Salisbury, Joshua Hathaway, Joseph Grant, William Lord, Rufus Pettibone, James Lynch, John Lay, John Storrs, Theodore Sill, Hezekiah L. Granger, James Porter, Warren Hecox, Gordon Needham, George Pomeroy, Charles Mason, Lester Holt, Oliver Bush, and James Hyde were candidates for Assembly.

sub_unit.name: Allegany
sub_unit.note: John J. Prendergast received 1 vote as John Prendergast.

sub_unit.name: Broome
sub_unit.note: Chauncey Loomis received 1 vote as Cauncy Loomis.
Bennet Bicknell received 1 vote as Benedick Buckell.

sub_unit.name: Cayuga
sub_unit.note: Chauncey Loomis received 1 vote as Chauncey Lomms.
John J. Prendergast received 3 votes as J.J. Prendergast.
Joshua Forman received 1 vote as Joseph Forman.
Calvin Bicknell received 3 votes as C. Bicknell.

sub_unit.name: Dryden
sub_unit.note: John J. Prendergast received 3 votes as J.L. Prendergast, 1 vote as J.H. Prendergast, and 1 vote as J. Prendergast.
Chauncey Loomis received 2 votes as C. Loomis, 1 as Chan. Loomis, and 1 vote as Chancy Lomins.
Philetus Swift received 5 votes as Phil. Swift, 1 vote as Phi. Swift and 1 vote as Philetus Smith.

sub_unit.name: Cortland
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), May 31, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 1, do not list individual candidate names. They report totals of 565 votes for the Republicans and 413 votes for the Federalists in Cortland County.
Jared Sanford received 4 votes as James Sanford.
Bennet Bicknell received 1 vote as Bennet Bick.

sub_unit.name: Homer
sub_unit.note: John J. Prendergast received 1 vote as John Prendergast.

sub_unit.name: Virgil
sub_unit.note: Bennet Bicknell received 5 votes as Bennet Bucknell.

sub_unit.name: Genesee
sub_unit.note: The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 25, does not list individual candidate names. It report totals of 1248 votes for the Republicans and 618 votes for the Federalists in Genesee County.

sub_unit.name: Henderson
sub_unit.note: John J. Prendergast received 3 votes as John J. Prendergrast and 1 vote as John J. Prendergass.

sub_unit.name: LeRay
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), May 25, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, lists 65 votes for Philetus Swift in LeRay.

sub_unit.name: Lewis
sub_unit.note: The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 29, does not list individual candidate names, only the parties. It reports totals of 267 votes for the Republicans and 182 votes for the Federalists in Lewis County; however, there are no results from the town of Pinkney.

sub_unit.name: Madison
sub_unit.note: The Pilot (Cazenovia, NY) reports a total of 858 votes for John J. Prendergast and 965 votes for Jared Sanford in Madison County. It does not list any votes for John J. Prendergast in Eaton, or for Jared Sanford in Eaton and Sullivan.

sub_unit.name: Niagara
sub_unit.note: Bennet Bicknell received 1 vote as Bennet Bickell.
John J. Prendergast received 1 vote as John Prendergast.

The Buffalo Gazette (Buffalo, NY) reports 376 votes for Chauncey Loomis, 373 votes for Bennet Bicknell, 364 votes for John J. Prendergast, and 225 votes for Joseph Kirkland in Niagara County. It does not list the town of Porter.

sub_unit.name: Oneida
sub_unit.note: John J. Prendergast received 1 vote as John Prendergast.

The Columbian (New York, NY), June 4, The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 8, Columbian Gazette (Utica, NY), and Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) report 1692 votes for Philetus Swift, 1686 votes for Chauncey Loomis, and 1680 votes for John J. Prendergast in Oneida County.

The Columbian (New York, NY), June 4, The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 8, and Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) report 2283 votes for Jared Sanford in Oneida County; however, the sum of totals per town is 2281.
The Columbian Gazette (Utica, NY) reports 2284 votes for Jared Sanford in Oneida County.

sub_unit.name: New Haven
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), June 4, The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 8, and Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) report 27 votes for Jared Sanford in New Haven.

sub_unit.name: Scriba
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), June 4, The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 8, and Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) report 8 votes for John J. Prendergast in Scriba.

sub_unit.name: Westmoreland
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), June 4, The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 8, and Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) report 63 votes for John J. Prendergast in Westmoreland.

sub_unit.name: Whitestown
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), June 4, The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), June 8, and Utica Patriot (Utica, NY) report 321 votes for Jared Sanford in Whitestown.

sub_unit.name: Onondaga
sub_unit.note: Jared Sanford received 29 votes as Jared Sanderford and 2 votes as Jared Sandf..

sub_unit.name: Pompey
sub_unit.note: The Columbian Gazette (Utica, NY) reports a Republican majority of 116 in Pompey.

sub_unit.name: Spafford
sub_unit.note: The Columbian Gazette (Utica, NY) reports a Republican majority of 20 in Spafford.

sub_unit.name: Ontario
sub_unit.note: Bennet Bicknell received 12 votes as Bennet Bricknell.
The Columbian (New York, NY), May 26, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, reports 1994 votes for John J. Prendergast; however, the sum of totals per town is 1991.
The Geneva Gazette (Geneva, NY) and Ontario Repository (Canandaigua, NY) report 2107 votes for Joseph Kirkland; however, the sum of totals per town is 2108.

The Geneva Gazette (Geneva, NY), Ontario Repository (Canandaigua, NY), The Columbian (New York, NY), May 26, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, report 2103 votes for Valentine Brother; however, the sum of totals per town is 2095.

The Geneva Gazette (Geneva, NY), Ontario Repository (Canandaigua, NY), The Columbian (New York, NY), May 26, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, report 2107 votes for Joshua Forman; however, the sum of totals per town is 2108.

The Geneva Gazette (Geneva, NY), The Columbian (New York, NY), May 26, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, report 2104 votes for Jared Sanford; however, the sum of totals per town is 2100.
Ontario Repository (Canandaigua, NY) reports 2104 votes for Jared Sanford; however, the sum of totals per town is 2090.

sub_unit.name: Honeoye
sub_unit.note: Ontario Repository (Canandaigua, NY) reports 54 votes for Jared Sanford in Honeoye.

sub_unit.name: Jerusalem
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), May 26, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, report 4 votes for John J. Prendergast in Jerusalem.

sub_unit.name: Mendon
sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY), May 26, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 28, report 34 votes for Bennet Bicknell in Mendon.

sub_unit.name: Otsego
sub_unit.note: The Otsego Herald (Cooperstown, NY), The Watch-Tower (Cooperstown, NY), The Columbian (New York, NY), May 14, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), May 18, report 1631 votes for Joseph Kirkland, 1629 votes for Valentine Brother, 1632 votes for Joshua Forman, and 1622 votes for Jared Sanford.

sub_unit.name: Saint Lawrence
sub_unit.note: John J. Prendergast received 15 votes as John Prendergast.

sub_unit.name: Schoharie
sub_unit.note: The Albany Argus (Albany, NY), June 24, The Columbian (New York, NY), July 11, and The Columbian. (For the Country) (New York, NY), July 13, report 976 votes for Philetus Swift in Schoharie County.

sub_unit.name: Seneca
sub_unit.note: Bennet Bicknell received 14 votes as Bennet Bickell and 3 votes as Bennet Bicknel.
John J. Prendergast received 1 vote as John Pendergrass.
The Columbian (New York, NY), July 9, reports 371 votes for Joseph Kirkland, 372 votes for Valentine Brother, 372 votes for Joshua Forman, and 374 votes for Jared Sanford in Seneca County.
